            },
            "advisory": "Affected versions of the Starlette package are vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) due to inefficient Range header processing behaviour in starlette.responses.FileResponse. The FileResponse._parse_range_header() routine parses multi-range requests and merges intervals using an O(n\u00b2) algorithm, so supplying many non-overlapping ranges causes quadratic CPU usage in routes that return FileResponse or are served via starlette.staticfiles.StaticFiles.",
